    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-03T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-03T07:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/3937</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-03T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 4, 3 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6643. Your telegram headed circular June 23.<note n="2" xml:id="d42fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_885">p. 885</ref>.</note> Am
                    in receipt of a note from Foreign Office giving text of a telegram which was
                    sent to British missions in neutral countries on June 13 as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The United States Government have instructed their diplomatic and
                            consular officers to co-operate fully with their colleagues of the
                            Allied Governments and to <pb facs="0138" n="892" xml:id="pg_892"/>
                            exchange information and furnish copies of reports relating to war
                            matters and restriction of enemy trade.</p>
                        <p>You should work in closest co-operation with your United States colleague
                            on the lines of instructions and request all consular officers under
                            your authority to do the same.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>With regard to last sentence your telegram I am informed as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>With regard to your inquiry as to co-operation in blockade measures here
                            in London Mr. <persName>Williams</persName> has already been in
                            communication with this Department on the subject and I can assure Your
                            Excellency that every possible facility will be extended to any
                            officials whom the United States Government may wish to appoint for the
                            purpose of co-ordinating and harmonizing the blockade policy of the two
                            countries.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
